 What We are Watching

 Mixed Fare

 Supriya Chowdhury and Madhabi Mukherjee 

 Janani

 Supriya Chowdhury and Madhabi Mukherjee come together in this social drama presented by Niva Arts. The story of a joint family and the problems that arise when the structure breaks down also features small-screen faces like Anuradha Roy, Sanghamitra Banerjee and Bodhisatwa Majumdar. Theatre thespian Gyanesh Mukherjee has a special role.

 Catch it at Tapan theatre, 3 pm and 6.30 pm, September 11

 Blues

 The stage adaptation of Katherine Mansfield?s short story The Fly. Directed by Amrita Panja. The performance will be preceded by the screening of The Hand of Fate, based on the same work, and followed by a discussion.

 Catch it at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm, September 12

 Deepdanda

 Directed by Kumar Roy, the latest Bohurupee production looks back to the kingdoms of Patuliputra, Magadh and Vaishali and a different worldview. Debesh Roy Chowdhury is assistant director.

 Catch it at Academy of Fine Arts, 6.30 pm, September 10

 Bhyablai Bhalo

 Theatre Passion presents this comic take on a good-at-heart village ruffian with Ramaprasad Banik as director and main actor.

 Catch it at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm, September 10




